---
import RedSectionHeader from "../common/RedSectionHeader.astro";
---

<section class="py-20 bg-white" id="bank-vs-insurance">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <RedSectionHeader
            title="The Great Debate: Bank vs. Insurance"
            className="mb-12"
        />

        <div class="prose prose-lg text-gray-700 max-w-none">
            <p class="mb-12 text-xl leading-relaxed">
                Once you decide to open a 3rd pillar, you face the most critical
                choice in the entire process: <strong
                    >Do you open it with a Bank or an Insurance company?</strong
                > Be careful. This decision often dictates whether you retire with
                maximum wealth or simply "safe" wealth—and it is costly to reverse.
            </p>

            <!-- 6.1 Bank Solutions Explained -->
            <div class="mb-16">
                <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
                    1. Bank Solutions (Depot Solution)
                </h3>
                <p>
                    A bank-based 3a is an investment account wrapped in a tax
                    shell. It is pure asset accumulation.
                </p>

                <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl mb-6">
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">How It Works:</h4>
                    <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 space-y-2 text-sm">
                        <li>
                            <strong>Opening:</strong> You open a specialised 3a account
                            (increasingly via app like VIAC, Finpension, Frankly).
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Investment:</strong> You choose a strategy (e.g.,
                            "Global 100" = 99% Stocks, 1% Cash). The bank buys ETF
                            or Index Fund shares for you.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Flexibility:</strong> You can pause contributions
                            anytime. No penalty. You can switch strategies anytime.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Costs:</strong> You typically pay a "All-in Fee"
                            (Management + Product costs), usually between 0.35% and
                            0.80% for digital providers.
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>

                <p><strong>The "Digital Revolution" Providers:</strong></p>
                <ul class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 list-none pl-0">
                    <li class="bg-white border rounded-lg p-4 shadow-sm">
                        <span class="font-bold text-blue-800 block mb-1"
                            >Finpension</span
                        >
                        <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 block mb-2"
                            >Fee: ~0.39%</span
                        >
                        <p class="text-sm">
                            Cost-leader. Ultra-customizable strategies. Flat
                            fee.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="bg-white border rounded-lg p-4 shadow-sm">
                        <span class="font-bold text-green-700 block mb-1"
                            >VIAC</span
                        >
                        <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 block mb-2"
                            >Fee: ~0.44% (can be lower)</span
                        >
                        <p class="text-sm">
                            First mover. excellent app. Free cash portion.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="bg-white border rounded-lg p-4 shadow-sm">
                        <span class="font-bold text-yellow-600 block mb-1"
                            >True Wealth</span
                        >
                        <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 block mb-2"
                            >Fee: 0.0% (Platform) + Product</span
                        >
                        <p class="text-sm">Auto-pilot robo-advisor approach.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="bg-white border rounded-lg p-4 shadow-sm">
                        <span class="font-bold text-red-600 block mb-1"
                            >Traditional Banks (UBS/CS/Kantonalbanks)</span
                        >
                        <span class="text-xs text-gray-500 block mb-2"
                            >Fee: 1.2% - 1.8%</span
                        >
                        <p class="text-sm">
                            Often legacy funds with high "Active Management"
                            fees. Generally not recommended for pure growth.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <!-- 6.2 Insurance Solutions Explained -->
            <div class="mb-16">
                <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
                    2. Insurance Solutions (Police 3a)
                </h3>
                <p>
                    An insurance-based 3a is a <strong>mixed product</strong> combining
                    savings with risk protection (death/disability).
                </p>

                <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl mb-6">
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">How It Works:</h4>
                    <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 space-y-2 text-sm">
                        <li>
                            <strong>Contract:</strong> You sign a binding contract
                            to pay CHF X per year for Y years (e.g., until age 65).
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Split:</strong> Your premium is split. Part goes
                            to savings, part to risk premiums (insurance coverage),
                            and part to administrative costs.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Guarantees:</strong> Often includes a guaranteed
                            minimum payout or capital protection.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Commitment:</strong> "Forced Savings" - pausing
                            payments is difficult or freezes the policy, often converting
                            it to a "paid-up" policy with losses.
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>

                <div
                    class="bg-yellow-50 border-l-4 border-yellow-400 p-4 text-sm mb-6"
                >
                    <strong>Warning:</strong> Insurance policies typically have low
                    "Surrender Values" in the first 5-10 years. If you leave Switzerland
                    after 3 years and cash out, you might get back <em>less</em> than
                    you paid in due to upfront commission and structuring costs.
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 6.3 Detailed Comparison -->
            <div class="mb-16">
                <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
                    Head-to-Head Comparison
                </h3>

                <div class="overflow-x-auto">
                    <table
                        class="min-w-full text-sm border-collapse border border-gray-300"
                    >
                        <thead>
                            <tr class="bg-gray-800 text-white">
                                <th
                                    class="p-3 text-left border border-gray-700 w-1/4"
                                    >Criteria</th
                                >
                                <th
                                    class="p-3 text-left border border-gray-700 w-1/3"
                                    >Bank / Fund Solution</th
                                >
                                <th
                                    class="p-3 text-left border border-gray-700 w-1/3"
                                    >Insurance Solution</th
                                >
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr class="bg-white">
                                <td class="p-3 border font-bold">Flexibility</td
                                >
                                <td class="p-3 border text-green-700 font-bold"
                                    >High (Stop/Change anytime)</td
                                >
                                <td class="p-3 border text-red-700"
                                    >Low (Contractual obligation)</td
                                >
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                                <td class="p-3 border font-bold"
                                    >Cost Transparency</td
                                >
                                <td class="p-3 border"
                                    >High (TER easily visible)</td
                                >
                                <td class="p-3 border"
                                    >Low (Mixed in premiums)</td
                                >
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="bg-white">
                                <td class="p-3 border font-bold"
                                    >Risk Protection</td
                                >
                                <td class="p-3 border text-red-700"
                                    >None (Pure Assets)</td
                                >
                                <td class="p-3 border text-green-700 font-bold"
                                    >Yes (Death, Disability Waivers)</td
                                >
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                                <td class="p-3 border font-bold"
                                    >Expected Return</td
                                >
                                <td class="p-3 border text-green-700 font-bold"
                                    >Higher (100% invested)</td
                                >
                                <td class="p-3 border"
                                    >Lower (Risk premiums deducted)</td
                                >
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="bg-white">
                                <td class="p-3 border font-bold">Best For</td>
                                <td class="p-3 border"
                                    >Wealth Accumulation, Expats</td
                                >
                                <td class="p-3 border"
                                    >Need for Family Protection, Discipline</td
                                >
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 6.6 Which is Best for Expats? -->
            <div class="mb-16">
                <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
                    The Expat Verdict
                </h3>

                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
                    <div
                        class="bg-white p-6 shadow-lg rounded-xl border-t-4 border-green-500"
                    >
                        <h4 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">
                            Why Banks/Apps Win for 90% of Expats
                        </h4>
                        <ul class="space-y-4 text-sm">
                            <li class="flex gap-3">
                                <span class="font-bold text-green-500 text-lg"
                                    >1.</span
                                >
                                <span
                                    ><strong>Mobility:</strong> Expats move. If you
                                    leave CH in 4 years, a bank solution lets you
                                    withdraw the full market value. An insurance policy
                                    might have a "surrender penalty" eating your profits.</span
                                >
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex gap-3">
                                <span class="font-bold text-green-500 text-lg"
                                    >2.</span
                                >
                                <span
                                    ><strong>Return on Investment:</strong> Since
                                    you likely have a pension gap, you need growth.
                                    Being 100% invested in equities via Finpension/VIAC
                                    offers better long-term compounding than a capital-guaranteed
                                    insurance product.</span
                                >
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div
                        class="bg-white p-6 shadow-lg rounded-xl border-t-4 border-blue-500"
                    >
                        <h4 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">
                            When to Choose Insurance
                        </h4>
                        <ul class="space-y-4 text-sm">
                            <li class="flex gap-3">
                                <span class="font-bold text-blue-500 text-lg"
                                    >1.</span
                                >
                                <span
                                    ><strong>Family Security:</strong> If you are
                                    the sole earner and have young children, the "Premium
                                    Waiver" (Prämienbefreiung) is powerful. If you
                                    become disabled, the insurance company <em
                                        >continues paying your pension
                                        contributions for you</em
                                    > until you retire.</span
                                >
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex gap-3">
                                <span class="font-bold text-blue-500 text-lg"
                                    >2.</span
                                >
                                <span
                                    ><strong>Forced Discipline:</strong> If you know
                                    you are "bad with money" and will skip voluntary
                                    bank transfers, the bill from the insurance company
                                    keeps you on track.</span
                                >
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="mt-8 bg-gray-100 p-6 rounded-lg">
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900">
                        The "Split" Strategy (Best of Both Worlds)
                    </h4>
                    <p class="text-sm mt-2">
                        Many savvy advisers recommend separating the two needs.
                        Open a <strong>Bank 3a</strong> for your maximum savings to
                        get growth. Separately, buy a pure <strong
                            >Term Life Insurance (Todesfallrisiko)</strong
                        > policy for protection. It’s cheaper, transparent, and if
                        you stop paying the insurance, you don’t lose your savings
                        pot—they are decoupled.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
